item.title: PortForwarding
item.dc:creator: @iaboni iaboni
item.description:
@iaboni wrote:

ohhhh… thats weird did you make sure your typing the right default gateway because if you are using ipconfig /all two default gateways would show one is wrong one is right, in which case use the one that works. Sorry but that usually does not happen to me as my router is Linksys, if that does not work, check for some tuts on arris port fowarding, otherwise a new router might be needed. Go to http://portforward.com/ press ctrl f and search arris then scroll down the list of router types, click your router type then ctrl f rune, wherever it shows 7777 change to 43594 (once you click into rune you will understand this part).

Read full topic
